On Fri, Apr 16, 2010 at 1:07 AM, Kerry McGinn <ajmcginn(-at-)comcast.net> wrote:
> This likely has no relevance to this dialogue, but I can tell you first-hand
 that a blown piston will cause blue smoke to gush out the back and also
 splatter specks of oil all over the rear hatches and bumper.

I did this to a Beetle once, but rather than splattering oil out the
exhaust, the blowby from the blown cylinder pushed the oil out the
crankcase vent and soaked the entire engine compartment besides the
speckles that made their way onto the decklid.

